Caption: Dendrocollybia racemosa - Branched shanklet Not my find but a collaborative effort to collect and record this rare species. Iâ€™m thrilled to get the opportunity to witness this one. The location has been recorded, and pending permissions, a sample will be making its way to Kew Gardens to be included in their genome sequencing projects and the national collection. Found by: Nicky Freeman Collected & record by: Iona Fraser @ashdownforage The species is characterised by its unusual stem, which is covered with short lateral branches. The branches often produce spherical slimeheads of translucentÂ conidiophoresÂ  on their swollen tips. The conidiophores produce conidia (asexualÂ spores) byÂ mitosis. Because the fungus can rely on eitherÂ sexualÂ orÂ asexualÂ modes of reproduction, fruit bodies sometimes have reduced or even missing caps. The unusual stems originate from black pea-sized structures calledÂ sclerotia. TheÂ anamorphicÂ form of the fungus, known asÂ TilachlidiopsisÂ racemosa, is missing the sexual stage of itsÂ life cycle. It can reproduce at relatively low temperatures, an adaptation believed to improve its ability to grow quickly and fruit on decomposing mushrooms. (Info via Wikimili) #allthingsfungi

Caption: Did you know that improper storage of grains and nuts could result in the production of a potent toxin? Aflatoxin B2 is mainly produced by the fungi Aspergillus flavus. Aflatoxin-producing molds are commonly detected in inadequately stored agricultural produce, including maize, rice, cassava, cottonseed, millet, sorghum, sesame seeds, sweetcorn, chili peppers, tree nuts, sunflower seeds, spices, and wheat. Aflatoxin B2, while not as toxic as Aflatoxin B1, can affect children, leading to delays in development and stunted growth. Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espÃ©cie Ã© um saprÃ³fito ou parasita especÃ­fico de espÃ©cies do gÃ©nero Betula. Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Labels: Fungus Polyporales Mushroom Close-up Trunk Medicinal mushroom Inonotus Natural material Macro photography Agaricomycetes
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Caption: Hereâ€™s what big ph*rm@ doesnâ€™t want you to knowâ€¦ Mushrooms are revolutionizing modern medicine! From boosting immunity to sharpening your mind, these versatile fungi offer a bounty of health benefits that are hard to ignore. What really makes them game changers are these key ingredients: - Polysaccharides - complex sugars that stimulate the immune system and have been shown to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects. - Beta-glucans - type of soluble fiber that helps regulate the immune system by binding to immune cells and stimulate them to attack invading pathogens, while also reducing inflammation in the body. - Active hexose correlated compound - nutritional product extracted from a variety of mushrooms that is commonly used to prevent and treat cancer. It contains a mixture of the polysaccharides, amino acids and minerals. I have experienced the amazing benefits first hand. My go-tos are @real_mushrooms and @thegeniusbrand. Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Caption: A critically endangered fungus - Tea-tree Fingers. This colony was only recently discovered by colleagues and is bigger than all the other previously known fruiting bodies combined. And it's the only colony within a National Park. The whacky thing is it feeds on another couple of specific species of fungi, so to conserve this fungus, we must conserve its hosts first. The other colonies are threatened by sand mining activity. #teatreefingers #rememberthewild #wildvictoria #VicOurNature #fungimap #endangered #SaveWesternportWoodlands

Post ID: 2895721991937798514
Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Labels: Fungus Polyporales Trunk Mushroom Medicinal mushroom Inonotus Agaricomycetes Pezizales Hen-of-the-wood Northern copperhead Boa constrictor
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity
